-- Libya Asks Mauritania to Extradite Qaddafi Intelligence Chief
-- B y   O u d a a   M a r o u f
-- 2012-07-03T14:24:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-03/libya-asks-mauritania-to-extradite-qaddafi-intelligence-chief.html
Libya ’s National Transitional Council
asked Mauritania to extradite Abdullah al-Senussi, the head of
intelligence services in Muammar Qaddafi’s government,
Saharamedias reported, without citing anyone.  Mustafa Abdel Jalil, chairman of the NTC, said Al-Senussi
will receive a just trial in Libya, the private online news site
reported. Al-Senussi was arrested by Mauritanian police in
Nouakchott, the North African nation’s capital, on March 17, it
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Oudaa Marouf in Nouakchott at 
 moudaa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
